reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not quite slim fit but decent low-budget buy.
reviews.reviewText: I am a black male, 6’3” and about 208lbs. I am pretty lean in build. I have decent arm size but they’re not bulky. I ordered 3 shirts size 15 1/2, 34/35 (White, Almond and Sundew). For the price, these shirts are okay. Just okay. The almond was the most opaque of the 3. The sundew and white were pretty see-through, but that’s kind of normal to me for lighter colored shirts. I tried on a thicker white dress shirt I own and could still see my white undershirt, but less than the one I purchased here.Honestly, I think these land somewhere in between regular and slim fit—as they’re not quite as baggy as regular fit, but not quite slim fit either. I decided to keep them because I plan to wear them underneath a suit most of the time so the transparency isn’t a big issue to me. Plus since my skin is darker, it’s somewhat normal to me to see my skin through the shirt depending on the shirt color. The rest of the fit is good—neck size is perfect and the shirt rests nicely on my body.A decent low budget buy.
